== Initialize Elastic ==

1. Copy elastisearch.yml into your elastic conf directory
2. Restart service elastic : sudo service elasticsearch restart
3. Initialize elastic indexes : ./init.sh localhost 9200

== Search example ==

GET http://localhost:9200/response/response/_search
{
  "query": {
    "match" : {
      "text" : {
        "query" : "ArMeS",
        "fuzziness": "AUTO"
      }
    }
  }
}

will return

{
  "_index": "response_1",
  "_type": "response",
  "_id": "AUzmq44s7fh1DRT02WJ8",
  "_score": 1.058217,
  "_source": {
     "text": "une arme",
     "rank": 3,
     "query": [
        {
           "text": "Comment se procurer"
        }
     ]
  }
}

== Index initialization with bonsai (on heroku) ==

Just use init.sh :

    ./init.sh 'https://secret_bonsai_with_auth_without_trailing_slash.url' 443
